    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Foliation: Contemporary foliation in ink in Hindu-Arabic numerals, upper left recto; catchwords every verso, lower left.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Layout: 13 long lines; border-ruled.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Script: Written in nastaʻlīq in black ink; pointed.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Decoration: Illuminated headpiece in gold and blue with text on cloudbands with gold fill with one section of 4 lines written on gold background (f. 1v-2r); final opening also written on cloudbands with gold fill (f. 188v-189r). Border-ruled in gold, red, blue with a page-opening frame rule in blue. Rubrications in red</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Binding: Mottled leather over pulpboard with gold tooled frame; black leather doublure; blue painted edges.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Origin: The item was copied in Muḥammadʹābād, Banāras in 1245 AH, 1830 CE (f. 189r); the scribe is not named, but is likely the same as the author.</subfield>
    </datafield>
